            <p>CENTRAL COMMITTEE OF THE BARON DE HIRSCH FUND<lb/>
                EXECUTIVE OFFICE&#44; NO. 45 BROADWAY&#44; ROOM 163.<lb/>
                A. S. SOLOMONS&#44; GENERAL AGENT<lb/>
                NEW YORK&#44; July 8&#44; 1897.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>	
                546 North Fifth Street&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Doctor&#58;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>The old hopeful adage &#34;All<lb/> things come to him who waits&#34; finds a grat&#45;<lb/>ifying illustration in the news we get from<lb/> the Baroness de Hirsch&#44; and while I hope it<lb/> will prove a stimulus to others who may be<lb/> well inclined to our Seminary&#44; I trust that<lb/> the large sum received will be used to the<lb/> best advantage.<lb/></p> 
            <p>With regards&#44; I am&#44;<lb/> Yours truly&#44;<lb/> A S Solomons<lb/></p>
            </body>
